        <type>int</type>
        <definition>int XVersion_Pack</definition>
        <argsstring>(XVersion *InstancePtr, u16 *PackedVersionPtr)</argsstring>
        <name>XVersion_Pack</name>
        <param>
          <type>XVersion *</type>
          <declname>InstancePtr</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>u16 *</type>
          <declname>PackedVersionPtr</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Packs a version into the specified packed version. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Versions are packed into the configuration ROM to reduce the amount storage.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>points to the version to pack. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>PackedVersionPtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>points to the packed version which will receive the new packed version.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para></para></simplesect>
A status, XST_SUCCESS, indicating the packing was accomplished successfully, or an error, XST_INVALID_VERSION, indicating the specified input version was not valid such that the pack did not occur <linebreak/>
<linebreak/>
 The packed version pointed to by PackedVersionPtr is modified with the new packed version if the status indicates success.</para><para><simplesect kind="note"><para></para></simplesect>
None. </para>        </detaileddescription>
