      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__common_1gacc5446415b912932b8a428ca698094d5" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>int</type>
        <definition>int XVersion_FromString</definition>
        <argsstring>(XVersion *InstancePtr, char *StringPtr)</argsstring>
        <name>XVersion_FromString</name>
        <param>
          <type>XVersion *</type>
          <declname>InstancePtr</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>char *</type>
          <declname>StringPtr</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Initializes a version from a null terminated string. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Since the string may not be a format which is compatible with the version, an error could occur.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>points to the version which is to be initialized. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>StringPtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>points to a null terminated string which will be converted to a version. The format of the string must match the version string format which is X.YYX where X = 0 - 9, YY = 00 - 99, Z = a - z.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para></para></simplesect>
A status, XST_SUCCESS, indicating the conversion was accomplished successfully, or XST_INVALID_VERSION indicating the version string format was not valid.</para><para><simplesect kind="note"><para></para></simplesect>
None. </para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
